{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 10:26:04.649978", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and goals\\n- Detect anomalies\\n- Localize faulty devices (if any)\\n- Identify root cause\\n\\nSummary assessment\\n- Overall network health: Normal. End-to-end reachability between hosts is good, control plane (eBGP) is established across the fabric, and routing tables are consistent with the described Clos topology.\\n- No service-impacting anomalies detected.\\n\\nEnd-to-end reachability\\n- pc_0_0 ↔ pc_0_1: 0% loss both directions, RTT ~2.6–3.2 ms. Indicates working data plane across leaves/spines/super-spine.\\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: avg RTT 3.21 ms\\n  - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0: avg RTT 2.64 ms\\n\\nControl plane status (eBGP)\\n- Leaf routers:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) peers up with spine_router_0_0 (172.16.0.4) and spine_router_0_1 (172.16.0.8). BGP table includes:\\n    - 10.0.0.0/24 locally originated\\n    - 10.0.1.0/24 learned via both spines; best via 172.16.0.4 (spine_router_0_0)\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201) peers up with spine_router_0_0 (172.16.0.6) and spine_router_0_1 (172.16.0.10). BGP table includes:\\n    - 10.0.1.0/24 locally originated\\n    - 10.0.0.0/24 learned via both spines; best via 172.16.0.6 (spine_router_0_0)\\n\\n- Spine routers:\\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) peers up with super_spine_router_0 (172.16.0.0), leaf_router_0_0 (172.16.0.5), leaf_router_0_1 (172.16.0.7).\\n    - Receives 0 prefixes from super-spine; receives 1 prefix from each leaf (total 2 prefixes), which is sufficient for correct forwarding.\\n    - RIB shows:\\n      - 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.5 (leaf 0)\\n      - 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.7 (leaf 1)\\n  - spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101) peers up with super_spine_router_0 (172.16.0.2), leaf_router_0_0 (172.16.0.9), leaf_router_0_1 (172.16.0.11).\\n    - Receives 2 prefixes from super-spine and both leaves (multiple paths per prefix visible).\\n    - Best paths selected to leaves as expected:\\n      - 10.0.0.0/24 best via 172.16.0.9 (leaf 0)\\n      - 10.0.1.0/24 best via 172.16.0.11 (leaf 1)\\n\\n- Super-spine:\\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000) peers up with both spines (172.16.0.1 and 172.16.0.3).\\n  - Learns both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 from both spines; selects best path via spine_router_0_0 (172.16.0.1) for both.\\n  - Advertises best paths to spine_router_0_1 (which receives them) and, per BGP loop-avoidance and bestpath behavior, does not advertise those best paths back to spine_router_0_0.\\n\\nRouting and next-hop consistency\\n- Leaves have connected /31s to both spines, and each advertises its /24 to both spines.\\n- Spines have connected /31s to both leaves and to the super-spine, and learn both leaf /24s.\\n- Super-spine has /31s to both spines and learns both /24s from both sides; selects best via spine_router_0_0, consistent with deterministic tie-breaks (e.g., lower neighbor IP/ID).\\n\\nObserved behaviors and their explanations\\n- Asymmetric prefix reception at spines from the super-spine:\\n  - spine_router_0_0 shows PfxRcd 0 from super-spine; spine_router_0_1 shows PfxRcd 2.\\n  - Root cause: On the super-spine, the best path for both /24s is via spine_router_0_0. BGP does not advertise a route back to the neighbor it learned the best path from (it would contain the neighbor’s AS in the AS_PATH and is not the best to advertise elsewhere). Without add-paths, non-best alternatives are not advertised. Therefore, 65100 legitimately receives 0 from 65000, while 65101 receives 2. This is expected and not an error.\\n\\n- Presence of multiple paths on spine_router_0_1 (including via super-spine and via the other leaf):\\n  - This is expected in an EBGP Clos without restrictive policies: EBGP-learned routes are re-advertised to other EBGP neighbors, subject to AS-path loop prevention. Spine_router_0_1 therefore sees:\\n    - Direct leaf-originated path\\n    - Path via super-spine\\n    - Occasionally path via the other leaf as transit (AS-path shows intermediate ASes). Only the best is selected; others remain as alternatives.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- No faulty devices identified. All EBGP sessions are established and stable; RIBs/FIBs match topology; host reachability is normal.\\n\\nRoot cause analysis\\n- No outage or misrouting detected.\\n- The only noteworthy asymmetry (super-spine advertising to one spine but not the other) is due to BGP best-path selection and standard loop-avoidance behavior, not a fault.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- The fabric is operating normally: full host reachability, correct BGP adjacencies, and consistent routing across leaves, spines, and super-spine.\\n- No anomalies requiring remediation were found., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='793feaf5-4d58-4ae1-86d7-35fdbae5e161'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
